      <title>[Letter] 1815 Jan. 30, Sugar Hill [to] Peter Hardeman, Camp Jackson, New Orleans / Thomas. Hardeman</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter dated January 30, 1815 from Thomas Hardeman to his son Peter Hardeman near New Orleans. In the letter, Thomas expresses grief and regret that two of his sons had been captured as prisoners of war by the British in New Orleans; he is optimistic that they will return home safely.</abstract>
